begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, we had a discussion about how often we've participated in these surveys. We talked a little bit about how there were some webcam issues because it seemed to cut out a bit at the beginning.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked about how things were going where we were living. We also talked about what we do for a living and found that we had a lot in common with our professions.
end_memory_text: Toward the end of the conversation, my partner and I talked about our professions. We talked about how we could help other people and encouraged each other to keep going in our professions and to not let negative feelings dominate our lives.
rest_of_day_open: It's hard to imagine the future, but I'm hoping the rest of my week goes well. There are some things that I definitely need to get done. I'm also hoping for some downtime so I can relax and maybe watch some television. Overall, I'm really hoping I get to visit my niece and nephew this week.
critical_positive: The conversation worked really well after a bumpy start due to technical issues. After those issues were resolved, we had a good time conversing, I would think. We had a lot in common with our professions, so that helped keep the conversation moving forward. She was very friendly and helped put me at ease, so it was comfortable.
critical_negative: There was not really anything that did not work well in our conversation besides a few technical issues at the beginning. We seemed to have a lot in common and focused on those issues. There were maybe a few seconds of silence when we did not know what exactly to say, but we overcame them rather quickly.

begin_memory_text: I noticed my chat partner was outside so I commented on that; and then we talked about the states we lived in. He was in Tennessee and I am in Virginia. He said he used to live in Chicago and we talked about that a little because I am familiar with Chicago and love it.
middle_memory_text: We talked about what we do for a living and how COVID affected that. We are both writers, and he said his productivity increased. I said I was able to work from home and achieve a better work/life balance.
end_memory_text: We talked about various writing ventures, what we planned to do for the holidays, a recent movie he had seen, and we wished each other good luck in our ventures.
rest_of_day_open: Since it is already Thursday, I only have one work day in "the rest of my week" before the weekend. I have a couple of meetings tomorrow that I'm actually looking forward to, so I can get clarification on project needs. I hope to be able to have those meetings, make a solid work plan for the next week, and finish out the day with organization and small tasks before going for a long, sunny walk at the end of the day and falling onto the couch for Friday night TV time!
critical_positive: We were both friendly - and although we had technical issues, we were both patient with them and agreed we would see the 25-minute conversation through even if we got kicked offline here and there. Also, we share the same profession so we had a good jumping-off point to go on.
critical_negative: He didn't ask me as many questions as I asked him, so at times the conversation may have lagged a little. I was able to overcome that because I actually interview people for a living so it wasn't a problem. He seemed a little younger than I am which might have made me self-conscious about the things I talked about and asked, etc.
